        <h2>Types of Boilers We Install</h2>
        <p>Choosing the right type of boiler for your home is crucial for efficiency, comfort, and long-term cost savings. At Hixa Heating, we're experts in all three main types of domestic boilers, and we'll help you select the perfect system for your property. Here's a detailed guide to help you understand the differences between each type:</p>
        
        <h3>Combi Boilers (Combination Boilers)</h3>
        <p>Combi boilers are the most popular choice in the UK, and for good reason. These compact units provide both central heating and instant hot water on demand, without the need for a separate hot water cylinder or cold water storage tank. This makes them ideal for properties with limited space, such as flats, apartments, and smaller homes.</p>
        
        <p>The main advantages of <a href="/combi-boiler-installation/">combi boilers</a> include instant hot water whenever you turn on a tap, lower installation costs compared to system boilers, and excellent energy efficiency since they only heat water when you need it. They're perfect for homes with one or two bathrooms and good mains water pressure. Modern combi boilers are incredibly compact and can be fitted neatly in a kitchen cupboard, freeing up valuable storage space elsewhere in your home.</p>
        
        <p>However, combi boilers may not be suitable for larger properties with multiple bathrooms in simultaneous use, as the flow rate can be limited by your mains water pressure. If you have a large family or frequently use multiple taps and showers at once, a system boiler might be a better choice.</p>
        
        <h3>System Boilers</h3>
        <p>System boilers are designed for homes with higher hot water demands. They work with a hot water cylinder (usually stored in an airing cupboard) that stores a large volume of pre-heated water, ready for use whenever you need it. This makes them ideal for larger properties with multiple bathrooms, where several people might want to use hot water simultaneously.</p>
        
        <p>The key benefits of system boilers include the ability to supply hot water to multiple outlets at the same time without loss of pressure, compatibility with solar thermal systems for improved energy efficiency, and faster hot water delivery compared to heating water on demand. They're particularly well-suited to properties with 3+ bedrooms and 2+ bathrooms.</p>
        
        <p>System boilers require more space than combis due to the cylinder, but they don't need a cold water tank in the loft (unlike conventional boilers), making them more compact than traditional systems. They're an excellent middle-ground option for larger homes.</p>
        
        <h3>Conventional Boilers (Regular/Heat-Only Boilers)</h3>
        <p>Conventional boilers, also known as regular or heat-only boilers, are the traditional type of heating system that includes a boiler, hot water cylinder, and cold water storage tank (usually in the loft). While they're less common in new installations, they're sometimes the best option for certain properties.</p>
        
        <p>These boilers are ideal for homes with traditional heating systems, older properties with multiple bathrooms, and houses where several people might want to use hot water at the same time. They're also compatible with solar thermal panels and can be a good choice if you're replacing an existing conventional system, as the pipework and infrastructure are already in place.</p>
        
        <p>The main drawback is that they require the most space of all boiler types, and once the hot water cylinder is empty, you'll need to wait for it to reheat. However, for the right property, they can be the most reliable and practical solution.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Not sure which type is right for you?</strong> Our expert engineers will assess your property, discuss your hot water usage patterns, and recommend the perfect boiler type for your specific needs. We'll explain all your options clearly, with no jargon or pressure to make a quick decision.</p>
        
